Love the food and prices

Verry good

Great food, good prices. Grilled blueberry muffin is to die for

My favorite place to eat on campus! They have the best scrambled egg in Boston!! I love the soft taste of scrambled egg, and most of other brunch places in local area cook too much. Bacon is also one of my favorite. I usually come here for brunch before class. Egg special is what I always have. The boss is a very nice guy. He makes you feel welcome.
Great food too bad they're not located in ct

Used to go here when I was on South Campus. Back in Boston for the weekend and we stopped in for old times sake and it was just as delicious as we remember. Loved the California and the coconut banana Nutella crepes!

Overall the food is mostly satisfying, well the omelets are (99% of my orders). The potatoes at times could be cooked a little more so they are not hard (rawish) and they could add some more flavor (a lil adobo goes a long way) and less rosemary to them. I've had my omelet well done a couple times, they can get busy quick and at times it feels understaffed.
Really good food
YUM! Very prompt and courteous service.

I am... Perplexed. I sometimes grab a takeout dinner here. The food is fine, nothing special, but the service is really bad. It's a struggle to get someone to take my order and then another struggle to get someone to actually ring it up. I think in the future I'll go elsewhere.

they serve Mediterranean breakfast lunch and dinner with choice of lamb, chicken or beef. pancake and toast in the morning is also good. esp the staff is welcoming and the service is not lazy though they make their dishes on the order.
